crops.presented_by: W. A. Archer

Note: for previous introduction see 97923.

crops.presented_by: C. A. Gardner, Government Botanist
crops.institution_involved: Department of Agriculture, Perth, Western Australia
crops.description: A graceful evergreen shrub with linear terete leaves and loose lateral clusters of reddish flowers; native to Australia. Seed material presented by C. A. Gardner, Government Botanist, Department of Agriculture, Perth, Western Australia. For previous introduction see 77277.

crops.presented_by: C. A. Gardner, Government Botanist
crops.institution_involved: Department of Agriculture, Perth, Western Australia
crops.description: An undershrub with usually simple stems 1 to 2 feet high and petioled basal leaves having nearly orbicular blades about 1 inch long; stem leaves bractlike and closely appressed; flexuose spikes 2 to 3 inches long in the axils of upper leaves bearing small white or violet flowers densely covered with silky white hairs. Native to Western Australia. For previous introduction see 93835.

crops.presented_by: C. A. Gardner, Government Botanist
crops.institution_involved: Department of Agriculture, Perth, Western Australia
crops.description: A tall shrub native to Australia with 3- to 5-lobed coarsely toothed leaves 1 to 3 inches long and large violet-purple flowers. For previous introduction see 95327.

crops.presented_by: C. A. Gardner, Government Botanist
crops.institution_involved: Department of Agriculture, Perth, Western Australia
crops.description: A low spiny evergreen shrub with very small lanceolate leaves about one-fourth inch long and small solitary axillary white flowers. Native to southwestern Australia.

crops.presented_by: C. A. Gardner, Government Botanist
crops.institution_involved: Department of Agriculture, Perth, Western Australia
crops.description: A low shrub with opposite fleshy semi-terete leaves crowded at the ends of the branches and small purplish flowers in the leaf axils.

crops.presented_by: F. H. Baker, Richmond, Victoria
crops.description: An Australian tree up to 300 feet high, with lanceolate leaves about 4 inches long, crowded umbels of small flowers, hemispheric fruits about one-fourth inch broad; leaves have a strong odor of peppermint and are rich in oil. For previous introduction see 93228.

crops.presented_by: F. H. Baker, Richmond, Victoria
crops.description: A form (variety Rosea) of Eucalyptus calophylla noted as having pink flowers.

crops.presented_by: F. H. Baker, Richmond, Victoria
crops.description: A medium-sized evergreen tree native to Australia with leathery lanceolate leaves and large corymbs of fragrant yellowish-white flowers.
